HELP VIEWER
===========
- Ctrl+g y opens this file in less.
- Press / to search, n/N for next/previous match, q to quit.

TMUX / PSMUX LOCK/UNLOCK KEYBINDS (mirrors the Zellij lock/unlock config)
==========================================================================

Prefix is Ctrl+g — the same gate key used in the Zellij lock/unlock config,
for identical muscle memory across both tools. Unlike the old hybrid layer,
there is no separate "no-prefix Alt layer" here except one deliberate
exception: Alt+hjkl for pane focus (same exception made in Zellij).

tmux's own prefix mechanism already reverts to passthrough after one
keystroke natively — you never "stay" in a captured state, no lock toggle
needed for one-shot actions.

Friendly help
-------------
Ctrl+g y                 Open this cheatsheet
Ctrl+g Y                 Show raw tmux/psmux key table

No-prefix exception (Alt, mirrors Zellij's one exception)
----------------------------------------------------------
Alt+h/j/k/l              Focus pane left/down/up/right
Alt+Left/Down/Up/Right   Focus pane left/down/up/right

Everything else below requires Ctrl+g first.

Panes behind prefix (Ctrl+g)
-----------------------------
Focus / selection
Ctrl+g h/j/k/l           Focus pane left/down/up/right (repeatable via repeat-time)

Pane management
Ctrl+g n                 New pane, smart split on the longest axis
Ctrl+g d                 New pane, split down
Ctrl+g r                 New pane, split right
                         (no "stacked" bind — tmux has no stacked-pane layout)
Ctrl+g x                 Close pane (asks y/n confirmation)
Ctrl+g z                 Toggle pane zoom/fullscreen
Ctrl+g f                 Floating-ish popup shell
Ctrl+g c                 Rename pane (sets pane title, prompts for text)

Resize — sticky table (Ctrl+g then +, -, or =)
------------------------------------------------
Ctrl+g + / - / =         Enter the Resize table
  h/j/k/l or arrows        Resize left/down/up/right by 3, repeats without prefix
  Esc / Enter / q          Exit back to normal typing

Move — sticky table (Ctrl+g m)
---------------------------------
Ctrl+g m                 Enter the Move table
  h/j/k/l or arrows        Swap focused pane with the one in that direction
  Esc / Enter / m          Exit back to normal typing

Tabs (tmux windows) behind prefix
------------------------------------
Ctrl+g t                 New tab/window
Ctrl+g ,                 Previous tab
Ctrl+g .                 Next tab
Ctrl+g 1..9              Go to tab 1..9
Ctrl+g Shift+t           Close tab/window
Ctrl+g Shift+r           Rename tab/window (prompts for text)
Ctrl+g i                 Move tab left
Ctrl+g o                 Move tab right

Layouts behind prefix
------------------------
Ctrl+g [                 Previous layout
Ctrl+g ]                 Next layout

Session / client behind prefix
------------------------------
Ctrl+g w                 Session manager (choose-tree)
Ctrl+g Shift+d           Detach client
Ctrl+g Ctrl+s            Enter copy-mode (scroll/search)
Ctrl+g Ctrl+q            Kill current session (WITH confirmation — a real dialog,
                         which the Zellij side does not have natively)

