Zellij <-> tmux parity (both use Ctrl+g as the gate)
--------------------------------------------------------
h/j/k/l        focus pane            (also Alt+hjkl, no prefix, both tools)
n/d/r          new pane (default/down/right) — no "s" stacked equiv in tmux
x              close pane (tmux confirms y/n; Zellij does not)
z              fullscreen/zoom
f              floating-ish popup shell
c              rename pane
+/-/=          enter sticky Resize table
m              enter sticky Move table
t              new tab
,/.            prev/next tab
1-9            go to tab N
Shift+t        close tab
Shift+r        rename tab
i/o            move tab left/right
[/]            prev/next layout
w              session manager
Shift+d        detach
Ctrl+s         scroll/copy-mode
Ctrl+q         quit (tmux confirms; Zellij needs the zj-quit plugin for that)
y/Y            cheatsheet / raw keylist

Notes
-----
- Prefix is Ctrl+g (changed from Ctrl+b/Ctrl+a in older setups).
- Some Alt combinations can still be intercepted by WezTerm or Windows Terminal;
  if Alt+hjkl misbehaves, use Ctrl+g h/j/k/l instead.
- tmux does not support stacked panes like Zellij; use split down/right instead.
